cs.CG, cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.GT, cs.SI. 

The paper deals with planar graph drawings and continuous transformations between them, which are topics related to computational geometry (cs.CG). The use of linear morphs and the analysis of their complexity suggest a connection to data structures (cs.DS) and algorithms (cs.DM). The study of planar graphs and their properties is also relevant to graph theory (cs.GT). Finally, the paper's focus on preserving certain properties of the graphs during the morphs, such as straight-line planarity, suggests a connection to computational topology (cs.SI).
